nst: Marcel Duchamp, John Cage und Merce Cunningham sowie Glenn Gould und Joseph Beuys. Aus fünf zeitgenössischen Fallbeispielen leitet sie eine interrelationale Ästhetik sowie einen kreativitätsbildenden Ansatz ab.  aMarcel Duchamp, John Cage, Merce Cunningham, Glenn Gould, and Joseph Beuys: from the work of these five trailblazers of transmedia art, this volume sets out the foundations of an inter-relational aesthetic and a basic, creative-educational stance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.) 0aCreation (Literary, artistic, etc.). 0aCreative abilityxPsychological aspects. 4aBildung. 4aGlenn Gould. 4aJohn Cage. 4aJoseph Beuys. 4aKreativität. 4aKulturelle Bildung. 4aKunst. 4aKunstpädagogik. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 4aMarcel Duchamp. 4aMedien. 4aMedienkunst. 4aMerce Cunningham. 4aTransmedial Entgrenzte Kunst. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh  aArt Education.  aArt.  aCreativity.  aCultural Education.  aEducation.  aFine Arts.  aGlenn Gould.  aJohn Cage.  aJoseph Beuys.  aMarcel Duchamp.  aMedia Art.  aMedia.  aMerce Cunningham.  aTheory of Art.  aTransmedial Art.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2016z9783110482812oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839436349zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isb